Ref ID: 31000-9502681611Classification: Software DeveloperCompensation: $120000.00 to $150000.00 yearlyRobert Half Direct is partnering with a Information Technology and Services company seeking a Python Developer to join their team. They specialize in the most-modern & proven technologies for their clients like Big Date Analytics, SAP, Cloud, mobility, Oracle, and Cross-platform services. There are many different data stores used by SAP LoBs to store data and should be subject to data encryption needs. The list of these Data Bases's include the following:* Relational databases (HANA, SQL Server, MySQL, MaxDB, Postgresql, Oracle)* NoSQL Databases (MongoDB)* Big Data systems (HDFS, HBase)* Others (Apache Solr)In order to ensure compliance with client Data:* Encryption requirements, Data Encryption/Key Management capabilities for all the above mentioned databases must be implemented.* Some of the above mentioned databases can use Data Custodian’s existing API, however, most of these databases rely on traditional Key Management standard interfaces like KMIP, PKCS#11 etc.* The plan is to implement the following compliant wrapper interfaces on top of Data Custodian KMS so that all these databases can be encrypted by various LoBs.Primary Responsibilities:* Implement a KMIP compliance wrapper interface that will translate KMIP protocol’s request/responses into Data Custodian’s REST API. This will allow MySQL, MaxDB, Postgresql, Oracle to be encrypted using Data Custodian KMS technology* Implement a Microsoft Extensible Key* Management (EKM) connector which will connect to Data Custodian KMS and provide encryption service for MS SQL Server databases.* Implement PKCS#11 library to serve as a bridge between PKCS#11 interface and Data Custodian KMS REST API
Experience with encryption / cryptography / encryption algorithms, protocols implementation. This includes hands on experience with FIPs level 3 HSMs, level 2 software KMSs, implementation experience of KMIP, PKCS11 protocols. (this is not about usage but the actual design and development of encryption service) * This position is a remote work from home opportunity for now and will eventually be moved into an office in Seattle, WA.Robert Half Technology matches IT professionals with some of the best companies on a temporary, project or full-time basis. Senior Software Engineer - 100% REMOTE Python/Django Development @ Fast-growing, Real Estate Tech SaaS Startup!This Jobot Job is hosted by: Luke SwiftAre you a fit? Easy Apply now by clicking the "Apply on company site" button and sending us your resume.Salary: $100,000 - $130,000A bit about us:Our powerful SaaS platform connects customers to real estate agents and help them save money in the process (sellers get a discount on commission, buyers get a rebate on their home purchase).We are now seeking several REMOTE Software Engineers (Mid/Senior level) with a background developing customer-facing SaaS and web-based applications experience, primarily with Python and Django. In this role, you'll do a lot of paired-programming with several members of our team the first few months in order to familiarize you with our existing systems and to build relationships with the rest of the Engineering team. You either should enjoy it or at least be willing to do paired-programming, otherwise this isn't the right opportunity for you. They should be well-versed with server-side technologies such as RESTful APIs, Amazon Web Services, CI/CD tools, and databases (PostgreSQL/NoSQL). Any experience with JavaScript and React.js is highly desired, but not required as we will ramp you up on them and any of the other technologies we use in no time. Lastly, this is a great time to get in on ground floor working alongside the Founders, CTO, and a key hire in shaping the way the organization's future goes. If this sounds like you, please apply now!Why join us?1. Marquee Product2. Massive Growth Opportunity3. Make a huge impact on the future of the organizationJob DetailsDay to Day:
 Develop, maintain, and enhance our powerful SaaS platform
 Take ownership by creating your own technical specs because as a small team, you are given personal ownership of the planning processes.
 Collaborate a lot with each other and with product stakeholders. 
 Participate in the spec processes for new features and epics on our roadmap, and you'll help others resolve issues when they have questions about certain parts of the codebase that you've gained familiarity with. 
 Establish strong working relationships with individuals inside and outside of Engineering, and you'll have a clear understanding of both our customer journey and the workflows of our internal stakeholders.
 Tackle small bugs and features while performing root-cause analysis for bugs independently, escalating to other teammates when you need a second set of eyes. 
 Use the business context you've picked up to discuss the priority of features and bugs in the backlog. 
 Advocate a new trend or tool that will help us perform root-cause analysis more easily when issues come up.
Requirements:
 4+ years of Software Development experience with Python (preferred) 
 At least 2 years of development experience on a consumer-facing SaaS or web-based application products
 Experience and/or willingness to participate in paired-programming (No Exceptions)
 Advanced with Python programming 
 Experience with Django or similar python web framework (Flask)
 Experience with RESTful API design & development
 Experience with RDBMs (PostgreSQL) and NoSQL databases
 Experience working within an Amazon Web Services (AWS) environment
Nice to have skills:, but not required: 
 Familiar with CI/CD and DevOps tools and best practices is highly desired
 Proficient with web technologies such as JavaScript, HTML, CSS is highly desired
 Experience with ReactJS is highly desired
Interested in hearing more? Easy Apply now by clicking the "Apply on company site" button.
\xa0

Develops and maintains operational and system level documentation. Must be able to apply SDLC concepts and have a proven track record of delivering solid, robust applications. Strong communication skills are required as position will interact with business owners.', 'The contractor will take a pass at all existing system alerts and create runbook for the on-call engineer to follow.', '', 'We are talking to other team to provide SRE support for the Bolt team, but the Bolt engineers are current busy supporting existing users, keeping the system running and creating high priority features for our users. We need to have a contractor to help us create all the run books so that we can easily transition the support workload to another SRE team. This contractor will review how the team is already running incidents and how to automate.', 'Top 2-3 skills client will be looking for when they review resumes?\xa0', '1) Site Reliability Engineer background', '2) Good documentation and communication skill', '3) Proficient in writing scripts (team uses Python and Bash)']

column4: ['At Parametric, we offer competitive salaries, generous benefits and opportunities for growth and development. We invite you to explore our available job opportunities listed below and look forward to having you become a part of our continued success!', '', '', '', 'General Description ', 'Parametric provides financial investment portfolio solutions to institutional clients, private clients, and financial advisors with a sharp focus on implementation excellence and client-specific customization. Our development team is composed of software engineers dedicated to building the software our company runs on. We rely on technical excellence, continuous integration, cloud technologies, and deep business collaboration to consistently deliver working software to our customers. What we offer is a chance to work with a group of people dedicated to finding better ways of delivering innovative software solutions for our clients.', 'We are looking for a smart, curious, self-motivated software developer to join our team.', 'ABOUT YOU', 'Maintenance', 'We support the software we have written to run our organization, but are committed to encompassing new technologies to extend and scale our existing portfolio to meet increasing demands. We document issues and provide analysis for future actionable improvements. The challenge we face is to add or change features in an existing architecture that makes measurable improvements without breaking existing functionality. To accomplish this, we rely heavily on automated testing and deployment.', 'TDD', 'We are committed to test driven development as an integral part of our development process.', 'Continuous integration ', 'We believe that "it works on my machine" is not good enough. Many software problems for organizations are deployment related. We minimize these issues by being sure to build and test our software using automation to continuously improve our processes.', 'Software Craftsmanship', 'We are committed to being a learning and teaching organization. We have an internship program in which we teach college students how to be professional developers. We share knowledge and ideas through pairing, weekly developer meetings, and one-on-one conversations. Your manager is your mentor, and will spend one-on-one time with you every week talking about your career and your aspirations.', 'Mentorship', "We are committed to improving the development team we have through the sharing of knowledge and ideas. As a senior engineer, you are an example to your peers on how to do things. You model the behavior and attitudes you wish your peers to emulate. As a leader, you will ensure that your team is clear about what they're building and why. You communicate best practices, ensure clear communication, and foster a collaborative and inclusive culture.", 'Leadership and Vision:', 'As a senior engineer, you should have experience leading teams and projects. You will be the point person on a team, learning and understanding the business requirements. You will often be responsible for the design of solutions to problems. With this comes the requirement to effectively communicate your decisions, designs and work with your team, the business, and everyone involved in the project.', 'The role', "Our average team consists of two developers, 1 QA representative, and a business contact. The business is in control of feature prioritization and scheduling. The technical team estimates work and decides how the features will be implemented. The whole team signs off on the software before it is released using our automated processes. You'll pair with developers and testers to write unit and integration tests and to implement features. You'll have your changes tested in a production-like environment with a complete set of services, databases, and applications. In addition, you'll be guiding the design of the software you work on and showcasing professional development practices to others in the group along the way. You will be looked at as a leader in the group.", "We try to always do the correct thing, however we're aware that there is room for improvement - things change, technologies evolve. You'll spot opportunities for improvement and efficiency gains, evangelize your solutions to the team, and see them implemented. You can affect change at Parametric.", 'Your professional growth', 'Your professional growth is important to us. To that end we:', 'Technologies we use', 'We use a mostly Microsoft .Net stack - SQL Server, C#, WPF, Winforms, IIS hosting, Signal-R with RabbitMQ as our transport for distributed processing, along with Github, Teamcity and Octopus to build and deploy.', 'Technologies we ARE TRANSITIONING TO', 'We are migrating to the AWS cloud platform. This includes existing software for portfolio performance, client reporting, market data, and portfolio accounting, as well as software to implement new products and help scale and extend market reach in our existing products. AWS provides managed container services such as ECS and EKS (managed Kubernetes) to orchestrate and deploy micro-services, as well as Serverless compute services such as API Gateway, Lambda functions, and analytic tools over big data like Kinesis, Athena, and Redshift.', 'Here is a non-exclusive list of technologies we use:', 'Job Requirements', '', '', '', 'Parametric is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to providing a work environment that is free of discrimination and harassment.\xa0 It does not discriminate against applicants or employees with respect to any terms or conditions of employment on account of race, color, religion, creed, national origin, ancestry, sex, sexual orientation, age, pregnancy, parenthood, physical or mental disability (actual or perceived), medical condition including genetic characteristics, marital status, citizenship status, military service, gender, gender identity or express, registered domestic partner status, domestic violence victim status, status with regard to public assistance, or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state or local laws.\xa0 Parametric also prohibits discrimination based on the perception that a person has any of those characteristics or is associated with a person who has or is perceived as having any of those characteristics.\xa0 This commitment applies to all persons involved in the operations of Parametric, and prohibits unlawful discrimination by any employee of Parametric, including supervisors and co-workers.\xa0 All employment decisions shall be consistent with the principles of equal employment opportunity.', 'The information on this website is for U.S. residents only and does not constitute an offer to sell, or a solicitation of an offer to purchase, securities in any jurisdiction to any person to whom it is not lawful to make such an offer. Investing entails risks and there can be no assurance that Parametric (and its affiliates) will achieve profits or avoid incurring losses. All investments are subject to potential loss of principal. Parametric does not provide tax or legal advice. Prospective investors should consult with a tax or legal advisor before making any investment decision. Please refer to the disclosure page for important information about investments and risks.']
